-{"id":"flywheel_connectors-id5bl","title":"TEST-FUZZ-X: ReplayWindow sliding-bitmap state-machine fuzz","description":"fcp_protocol::session::ReplayWindow (session.rs:720-797) is the per-session sliding-bitmap replay-protection for FCPS frame seq numbers. Distinct from HelloReplayWindow (p5ams) which is a (from,nonce) FIFO. ReplayWindow.check / check_and_update gate the per-frame MAC verification to prevent CPU-exhaustion attacks from replays. Properties: reject seq=0; accept first non-zero seq; reject immediate replay; reject in-window already-seen; reject out-of-window (too old); future seq updates highest_seq + shifts bitmap; check ⇔ check_and_update agreement on the same state. Once-gated anchors: window_size=128 boundary (seq=highest-127 in, seq=highest-128 out), bitmap-shift correctness on large jumps. Acceptance: fuzz/fuzz_targets/replay_window.rs with model-driven fuzz + 3 anchors. cargo +nightly check + clippy -D warnings clean.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"test","assignee":"SunnyMoose","created_at":"2026-04-27T22:34:03.164170Z","created_by":"jemanuel","updated_at":"2026-04-27T22:34:07.556254Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id":"flywheel_connectors-id5bl","title":"TEST-FUZZ-X: ReplayWindow sliding-bitmap state-machine fuzz","description":"fcp_protocol::session::ReplayWindow (session.rs:720-797) is the per-session sliding-bitmap replay-protection for FCPS frame seq numbers. Distinct from HelloReplayWindow (p5ams) which is a (from,nonce) FIFO. ReplayWindow.check / check_and_update gate the per-frame MAC verification to prevent CPU-exhaustion attacks from replays. Properties: reject seq=0; accept first non-zero seq; reject immediate replay; reject in-window already-seen; reject out-of-window (too old); future seq updates highest_seq + shifts bitmap; check ⇔ check_and_update agreement on the same state. Once-gated anchors: window_size=128 boundary (seq=highest-127 in, seq=highest-128 out), bitmap-shift correctness on large jumps. Acceptance: fuzz/fuzz_targets/replay_window.rs with model-driven fuzz + 3 anchors. cargo +nightly check + clippy -D warnings clean.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"test","assignee":"SunnyMoose","created_at":"2026-04-27T22:34:03.164170Z","created_by":"jemanuel","updated_at":"2026-04-27T22:35:37.579481Z","closed_at":"2026-04-27T22:35:37.578960Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"comments":[{"id":3101,"issue_id":"flywheel_connectors-id5bl","author":"jemanuel","text":"Shipped in commit 53900f5e. fuzz/fuzz_targets/replay_window.rs — 5 properties (seq=0 reject, check purity, check⇔check_and_update agreement, immediate-replay reject, highest_seq monotonicity) + 3 once-gated anchors (window_size=128 inclusive boundary at diff=127 vs reject at diff=128, large-jump bitmap clear, immediate replay). Distinct from p5ams HelloReplayWindow (handshake-layer FIFO). cargo +nightly check + clippy -D warnings clean.","created_at":"2026-04-27T22:35:37Z"}]}
 {"id":"flywheel_connectors-idk2k","title":"[REVIEW-CONVERGE][HIGH] fcp-bootstrap provider_session_registry race: concurrent acquire+finalize can tear down in-use Pkcs11 context","description":"crates/fcp-bootstrap/src/hardware_token.rs:1411-1441 (commit 965d9601 br-7s8ri) — finalize_pkcs11_context takes the registry Mutex, calls note_provider_session_close to decide should_finalize, DROPs the lock, then calls pkcs11.finalize() outside the lock. acquire_provider_context holds the lock across Pkcs11::new + initialize + note_provider_session_open. Race scenario: (1) thread A calls finalize, note_close returns true (last session), drops lock; (2) thread B calls acquire, takes lock, Pkcs11::new OK, pkcs11.initialize() returns CryptokiAlreadyInitialized because A has not yet run finalize() — initialized_here=false; (3) B note_provider_session_open records active=1, finalize_required=false; (4) B drops lock and starts using its Pkcs11 handle; (5) A finally calls pkcs11.finalize() on the now-shared underlying PKCS#11 runtime, tearing down B s context. Bs next C_* call fails with CryptokiNotInitialized. Suggested fix: hold the registry lock across pkcs11.finalize() so no acquire can observe a dangling already-initialized state between note_close and finalize. The lock contention window is short (a C_Finalize call) and finalize is rare. Alternatively, swap the order: finalize first then update the registry under lock, but that makes the recovery case (finalize error) harder. Simplest: hold the lock for the whole finalize_pkcs11_context body. Reviewer: cc_1 REVIEW-CONVERGE.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-23T22:08:38.261434Z","created_by":"jemanuel","updated_at":"2026-04-23T22:17:41.335187Z","closed_at":"2026-04-23T22:17:41.334233Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"comments":[{"id":2842,"issue_id":"flywheel_connectors-idk2k","author":"jemanuel","text":"Resolved in commit 684fd99b.

Fix: remove the drop(sessions) between note_provider_session_close and pkcs11.finalize() so the registry MutexGuard stays live across the actual finalize call. The guard now drops at end of scope AFTER finalize returns, serializing A's teardown against any B's acquire+initialize. No concurrent acquire_provider_context can observe the dangling 'already initialized but about to be finalized' state.

Lock hold time grows by one C_Finalize call (short + rare — only runs after the last session closes). Forward progress after a poisoned lock preserved via PoisonError::into_inner.

Alternative swap-the-order (finalize first, then registry update under lock) considered + rejected: a panic between finalize and note_close would desync the registry.

Verified: cargo test -p fcp-bootstrap 792 pass (699 lib + 23 + 9 + 61 integration), 0 fail. Clippy clean (only pre-existing unrelated docstring-backtick warning in error.rs).

No regression test added — exercising the race needs multi-threaded execution against a real PKCS#11 provider, which isn't hermetic enough for CI. The invariant is structural (single lock acquisition spans the close-decision and finalize call) and enforced by compiler scope-drop semantics on the MutexGuard.

— cod_4 / SunnyMoose","created_at":"2026-04-23T22:17:40Z"}]}
 {"id":"flywheel_connectors-iei8u","title":"TEST-CONFORMANCE-29: AdmissionController gc_stale_peers + record_auth_failure budget","description":"Two AdmissionController surfaces complementing br-d2uly + br-uekoy: (1) record_auth_failure tracks failed auth attempts in a sliding window and surfaces AuthFailureBudgetExceeded with retry_after — distinct from byte/symbol/decode budgets, (2) gc_stale_peers is the periodic memory-bound cleanup that prevents the per-peer table from growing unboundedly across distinct attacker NodeIds. Critical: gc MUST keep peers with inflight_decodes > 0 regardless of staleness (otherwise an active decode loses its inflight count). cc_2 domain (fcp-conformance + fcp-mesh).","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-27T22:26:09.960794Z","created_by":"jemanuel","updated_at":"2026-04-27T22:27:44.595677Z","closed_at":"2026-04-27T22:27:44.595223Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["conformance","mesh","tests"],"comments":[{"id":3094,"issue_id":"flywheel_connectors-iei8u","author":"jemanuel","text":"98ab9609 adds admission_gc_and_auth_failure_conformance.rs with 10 tests pinning record_auth_failure (under-budget happy path, over-budget AuthFailureBudgetExceeded with retry_after, per-peer isolation against credential-stuffing collateral damage, no-allocation-for-unrelated-peer) and gc_stale_peers (idle-old eviction, recent-keep, the CRITICAL invariant that peers with inflight_decodes>0 are kept across GC regardless of staleness, post-release eviction, empty-table no-op, peer-specific eviction). All 10 pass in <0.01s. Mid-stream threshold-arithmetic fix on the preserves_other test.","created_at":"2026-04-27T22:27:44Z"}]}
